01:49.333 --> 01:51.533
- I am innocent.
- I'm innocent.

01:51.533 --> 01:54.900
- I'm innocent.
- Innocent.

01:54.900 --> 01:56.767
- I'm innocent too.

01:56.767 --> 01:58.367
- I'm innocent.

01:58.367 --> 01:59.567
You go to any prison,

01:59.567 --> 02:01.066
you ask any guy
who's serving time

02:01.066 --> 02:03.600
and he'll tell you
he's in-no-cent.

02:03.600 --> 02:06.433
I got a bum rap,
I had a lousy lawyer.

02:06.433 --> 02:09.000
I was in Toledo
visiting my mama.

02:09.000 --> 02:11.400
Yeah, you'll hear
a whole pack of lies.

02:11.400 --> 02:14.433
But what about that one brother
who's telling the truth,

02:14.433 --> 02:17.233
the one who really is innocent?

02:17.233 --> 02:20.567
His voice is buried
so damn deep beneath the others,

02:20.567 --> 02:23.066
he's gonna grow hoarse
just trying to be heard.

02:32.467 --> 02:34.000
- Leo!

02:34.000 --> 02:36.033
- Leo Glynn is dead.

02:36.033 --> 02:41.200
I'm sorry, the reality
just hasn't sunk in.

02:41.200 --> 02:44.333
- I feel so bad,
you know?

02:44.333 --> 02:47.166
He and I hadn't been
getting along lately.

02:47.166 --> 02:50.100
- Well, we all had our
disagreements with Leo,

02:50.100 --> 02:54.200
but still, he was the best man
for the worst job.

02:54.200 --> 02:55.467
- Amen.

02:58.667 --> 03:02.100
- I spoke to his ex-wife
at the cemetery.

03:02.100 --> 03:04.500
She and his daughter
didn't want to make the drive,

03:04.500 --> 03:08.400
would I pack up
Leo's belongings.

03:08.400 --> 03:11.467
I don't think she has a clue
about my relationship with him.

03:11.467 --> 03:13.700
- Mary knew.

03:13.700 --> 03:16.633
She said she was happy
Leo had someone.

03:16.633 --> 03:20.467
She hated the idea of him being
all alone after the divorce.

03:20.467 --> 03:23.000
- Tim, I talked
to the governor

03:23.000 --> 03:24.900
about naming you the new warden.

03:27.500 --> 03:29.734
I'm sure Devlin jumped.

03:29.734 --> 03:31.100
- Well, he didn't say no.

03:31.100 --> 03:33.767
- Doesn't matter,
don't want the job.

03:36.633 --> 03:39.533
- This place needs a strong,
sensible hand, Tim.

03:39.533 --> 03:40.734
That's you.

03:42.700 --> 03:45.100
- Stanton has some
interesting hearsay.

03:45.100 --> 03:48.400
- Lionel Kelsch
whacked the warden

03:48.400 --> 03:50.734
and Willy Brandt.

03:50.734 --> 03:55.400
And before that, he helped
Brandt waste Mayor Loewen.

03:55.400 --> 03:56.734
- How do you
know this?

03:56.734 --> 04:00.600
- Kelsch is a bragger,
and I hate braggers!

04:00.600 --> 04:03.600
- All right, take Stanton
into protective custody.

04:03.600 --> 04:05.567
Bring Kelsch to the hole.

04:08.800 --> 04:10.500
- All right!

04:12.233 --> 04:13.633
- You ever been
in the hole, Kelsch?

04:13.633 --> 04:14.800
- No, sir.

04:14.800 --> 04:17.300
- First, you're naked,
so it's cold.

04:17.300 --> 04:20.367
Then you piss
and shit in a bucket.

04:22.233 --> 04:24.100
Worse, you're alone,

04:24.100 --> 04:27.367
utterly alone,
24 hours a day.

04:30.433 --> 04:31.567
Except for the meals, right?

04:31.567 --> 04:32.967
When you see the hacks?

04:32.967 --> 04:34.500
- Theoretically.

04:34.500 --> 04:39.367
See, some of these guys,
they forget to bring the food,

04:39.367 --> 04:44.600
especially to someone accused of
killing the man they respected.

04:44.600 --> 04:47.033
- Hm.
- Strip.

04:47.033 --> 04:50.467
- Um, McManus, wait.

04:50.467 --> 04:52.233
What are my alternatives?

04:52.233 --> 04:55.133
- You can give me the name
of the person that hired you.

04:56.567 --> 04:59.567
- I thought the governor's
eulogy of Glynn was very moving.

04:59.567 --> 05:01.600
- Oh, yeah?
I nodded off.

05:01.600 --> 05:03.600
- What does McManus
want to see me about?

05:03.600 --> 05:05.400
- I don't know, he just
told me to find you.

05:05.400 --> 05:07.066
- Think he'll get
the warden gig?

05:07.066 --> 05:09.100
- Never know.

05:14.200 --> 05:16.567
