What's wrong with her?

19:14.734 --> 19:17.633
- Claire asked me
for a second opinion.

19:17.633 --> 19:19.300
- Is she sick?

19:20.800 --> 19:22.367
- She's pregnant.

19:28.000 --> 19:30.433
- You asked to see me,
Father?

19:30.433 --> 19:33.367
- Yes, come in,
sit down.

19:33.367 --> 19:35.100
- What's this about?

19:35.100 --> 19:37.567
- Your being pregnant.

19:37.567 --> 19:39.867
I'm not trying to insinuate
myself into anything.

19:39.867 --> 19:43.300
I just wanted you to know
that if you want to talk...

19:46.800 --> 19:50.500
- What I tell you
remains between us, right?

19:50.500 --> 19:53.600
Because I could
lose my job.

19:53.600 --> 19:56.266
- I promise.

20:02.767 --> 20:08.333
- My relationship with men
in general has been disastrous,

20:08.333 --> 20:11.033
yet here I am
surrounded by them.

20:12.800 --> 20:15.300
Which is why...

20:15.300 --> 20:19.133
Father, since coming to Oz,
I have fucked a lot of men.

20:21.300 --> 20:22.800
Oh, yeah!

20:22.800 --> 20:24.700
A lot of prisoners.

20:27.834 --> 20:29.834
You're shocked.

20:29.834 --> 20:30.900
- In a way, yes.

20:30.900 --> 20:34.367
And in a way, no.

20:34.367 --> 20:38.300
- Now, I'm pregnant
by one of them.

20:38.300 --> 20:40.533
- You know which one?

20:40.533 --> 20:43.166
- Well, my best guess is
the baby'll be golden brown

20:43.166 --> 20:45.967
and marinated in salsa,

20:45.967 --> 20:49.233
which means
I can't raise him or her

20:49.233 --> 20:51.300
in my redneck
neighborhood.

20:51.300 --> 20:53.467
I can't afford to move.

20:53.467 --> 20:55.333
And if I could,
where would I go?

20:55.333 --> 20:57.000
Little Havana?

20:57.000 --> 20:58.633
I am screwed.

20:59.834 --> 21:01.967
- Claire, are you thinking of
having an abortion, because--

21:01.967 --> 21:03.600
- Oh, save your
breath, Father.

21:03.600 --> 21:06.133
You Catholics aren't the only
ones who are against abortion.

21:06.133 --> 21:09.934
- So, what are you
gonna do?

21:09.934 --> 21:12.967
- Take a leave of absence,

21:12.967 --> 21:15.734
drop the calf,

21:15.734 --> 21:20.033
and from then on,
keep my fuckin' legs crossed.

21:32.300 --> 21:34.700
- I'll never be
a father now.

21:36.033 --> 21:38.734
- Yeah, well, we all
got our problems.

21:46.767 --> 21:49.166
- Here's a story,
and it's true.

21:49.166 --> 21:50.533
Up in Vermont

21:50.533 --> 21:53.066
an inmate was caught
breaking into prison.

21:53.066 --> 21:55.233
He'd evidently slipped out
of his work camp,

21:55.233 --> 21:57.066
went to a nearby
convenience store,

21:57.066 --> 21:59.500
bought a case of beer
and a carton of cigs

21:59.500 --> 22:02.300
and then crawled back
under the fence,

22:02.300 --> 22:05.834
where he was arrested
by the C.O.'s.

22:05.834 --> 22:08.266
The man was sentenced
to six more months,

22:08.266 --> 22:09.900
and the poor motherfucker,

22:09.900 --> 22:11.800
he didn't even get
to keep the beer.

22:13.033 --> 22:14.166
You know what I'm saying?

22:14.166 --> 22:16.467
- okay, raise your arms.

22:16.467 --> 22:19.100
Turn around.

22:19.100 --> 22:21.066
Through here.

22:22.600 --> 22:25.600
- Jackson Vahue,
welcome to Oz.

22:25.600 --> 22:27.800
- It's not my first visit,
warden.

22:27.800 --> 22:29.400
- I know.

22:29.400 --> 22:31.000
- Since being paroled,

22:31.000 --> 22:32.500
I've tried my best
to keep other guys

22:32.500 --> 22:33.900
from making my mistake,

22:33.900 --> 22:36.066
you know, lecturing the kids
and gangs and stuff.

22:36.066 --> 22:38.233
- I'm happy you're here
to do the same.

22:38.233 --> 22:41.233
Younger prisoners look up to
a big basketballer like you.

22:41.233 --> 22:43.133
- Well, I hope they hear
what I have to say.

22:44.600 --> 22:46.467
- After you.

22:46.467 --> 22:48.400
- So, in conclusion,

22:48.400 --> 22:51.166
I just ask you to use
your time wisely and well.

22:51.166 --> 22:52.400
With any kind of luck,

22:52.400 --> 22:54.100
you can pull your
life back together...

22:56.734 --> 22:58.900
And get the fuck
out of Oz.

23:03.667 --> 23:06.000
- Hey,
can I get your autograph?

23:06.000 --> 23:08.567
- Officer Brass, you still
dancing down these halls?

23:08.567 --> 23:09.600
- Yup.

23:09.600 --> 23:11.400
Some of us ain't
as lucky as you.

23:11.400 --> 23:13.600
- You know, I had nothing to do
with that tendon being sliced.

23:13.600 --> 23:15.467
- Oh, I know.

23:15.467 --> 23:17.367
Hey, I bought season tickets
to the Knights,

23:17.367 --> 23:18.834
so, I'll be at the arena
every time you play.

23:18.834 --> 23:20.233
- Uh-huh.

23:20.233 --> 23:22.400
- Maybe after a game I can
come into the locker room,

23:22.400 --> 23:24.166
hang out,
meet the other players.

23:24.166 --> 23:26.233
- No, I don't think so.

23:26.233 --> 23:29.033
- Oh, okay, um...

23:29.033 --> 23:31.033
Let me ask you
something, Jackson.

23:31.033 --> 23:32.767
When you're out
on the court playing,

23:32.767 --> 23:36.433
all those eyes on you,
you ever wonder?

23:36.433 --> 23:38.100
- Wonder what?

23:38.100 --> 23:40.133
- Who's out there?

23:40.133 --> 23:42.533
There's a lot of crazies
in the world, man.

23:44.200 --> 23:46.133
- No, I'm not afraid.

23:46.133 --> 23:49.900
- Bro, you got
huge stundeens.

23:49.900 --> 23:51.467
Nice to see you again.

23:54.033 --> 23:55.533
- All right, fellas.

24:08.367 --> 24:09.734
- Dave.

24:11.533 --> 24:14.667
- Sean, Sean,
you threw me off my game.

24:16.834 --> 24:19.233
Sometimes I wonder
if I wanted to play pro ball

24:19.233 --> 24:21.066
because I loved
the game so much,

24:21.066 --> 24:24.300
or because I wanted everyone
to see how great I could shoot.

24:27.400 --> 24:29.033
Be adored by millions.

24:29.033 --> 24:32.500
- Money, women,
the whole rigmarole, huh?

24:32.500 --> 24:34.834
- I don't care about
the fringe benefits.

24:34.834 --> 24:37.033
I want to be famous.

24:37.033 --> 24:39.400
I don't want to die
being some gimpy, old guard

24:39.400 --> 24:41.433
at a half-ass prison.

24:41.433 --> 24:44.000
I don't want
to disappear.

24:44.000 --> 24:45.967
- Well, I mean,
what can you do?

24:45.967 --> 24:47.967
You play the hand
life deals you.

24:47.967 --> 24:51.033
- Sean, I know you did
what you think is right

24:51.033 --> 24:52.767
about Morales.

24:52.767 --> 24:55.333
I want to tell you,
I admire you.

24:55.333 --> 24:56.900
I always have.

24:56.900 --> 24:58.700
No hard feelings, huh?

25:01.934 --> 25:04.333
- Why do I feel like
you're saying goodbye?

25:04.333 --> 25:06.033
- I am.

25:06.033 --> 25:09.300
I've decided,
I'm quitting.

25:10.767 --> 25:12.233
- To do what?

25:12.233 --> 25:15.300
- Reshuffle the deck,
play a new hand.

25:25.967 --> 25:29.066
- This just in,
basketball star Jackson Vahue

25:29.066 --> 25:31.033
was shot at
this afternoon

25:31.033 --> 25:32.934
during practice
at the arena.

25:32.934 --> 25:34.500
The assailant,
David Brass,

25:34.500 --> 25:36.433
has been working
as a guard...

25:36.433 --> 25:38.367
- Oh, shit!
- Officer Murphy?

25:38.367 --> 25:41.233
- Vahue served time at Oswald
and says he barely knew Brass,

25:41.233 --> 25:43.433
though they did play
opposite each other

25:43.433 --> 25:45.166
in a prison
basketball game.

25:49.533 --> 25:52.700
- Here's a story,
and it's true.

25:52.700 --> 25:55.100
A municipal court judge
in Texas

25:55.100 --> 25:58.333
was indicted on four counts
of sexual misconduct.

25:58.333 --> 26:00.900
Seemed this judge
extorted sexual favors

26:00.900 --> 26:03.600
from the female relatives
of criminal defendants

26:03.600 --> 26:06.300
in exchange for reducing
the defendants' bond,

26:06.300 --> 26:08.567
or ordering their release.

26:08.567 --> 26:11.734
Hey, when you're horny,
you're horny.

26:12.800 --> 26:14.533
- Mr. Hoyt, thank you
for coming to see us.

26:14.533 --> 26:15.767
I'm Father Mukada.

26:15.767 --> 26:17.400
- How do you do?

26:17.400 --> 26:19.400
- Oh, and this is
Sister Peter Marie.

26:19.400 --> 26:21.266
- Sorry.
Hello, nice to meet you.

26:21.266 --> 26:22.767
- How do you do?

26:24.300 --> 26:26.600
This...

26:26.600 --> 26:30.700
this is
my first trip to a prison.

26:30.700 --> 26:34.100
- Oh, you haven't
visited Jaz before?

26:34.100 --> 26:35.900
- No.

26:35.900 --> 26:39.867
I'm not exactly sure what it is
that you want from me.

26:39.867 --> 26:44.133
- Well, we feel that in order
for Jaz to fully recover,

26:44.133 --> 26:48.300
he needs to deal with
certain emotional problems.

26:48.300 --> 26:50.200
- Yeah.

26:50.200 --> 26:54.600
You can't blame
Evangeline and me

26:54.600 --> 26:56.867
for the way
the boy turned out.

26:56.867 --> 26:59.467
We were good parents.

26:59.467 --> 27:02.033
I mean, we didn't
just give him things.

27:02.033 --> 27:04.100
We--we gave him love,

27:04.100 --> 27:05.900
plenty of love.

27:05.900 --> 27:10.066
But there was always something
not quite right about the boy

27:10.066 --> 27:12.467
from the very first day

27:12.467 --> 27:15.934
that we brought him home
from the orphanage.

27:15.934 --> 27:18.467
- Jaz was adopted?

27:18.467 --> 27:19.734
- Oh, yes.

27:19.734 --> 27:22.333
My wife and I
couldn't have children.

27:22.333 --> 27:24.300
We adopted three.

27:24.300 --> 27:26.767
- Have you ever tried
to find out more

27:26.767 --> 27:28.567
about Jaz's birth parents?

27:28.567 --> 27:33.533
- Yes, the father
died in prison.

27:33.533 --> 27:37.400
The mother lived
in Morrisville.

27:38.767 --> 27:41.934
Whether she still
lives there, who knows?

27:41.934 --> 27:43.934
- Mr. Hoyt, could I have
the information

27:43.934 --> 27:45.834
about Jaz's
birth parents?

27:45.834 --> 27:47.400
- Certainly.

27:47.400 --> 27:48.567
- Drink your juice.

27:48.567 --> 27:50.533
- No.
- Drink your juice.

27:50.533 --> 27:52.000
- No!

27:52.000 --> 27:53.967
- Drink the goddamn juice.

27:53.967 --> 27:55.467
- No, bitch!

27:58.133 --> 28:00.333
Get the fuck
out of my face!

28:03.266 --> 28:06.066
- Jessica, one of the hardest
things about working in Oz

28:06.066 --> 28:08.934
is trying to separate
the man from his crime.

28:08.934 --> 28:11.367
If you can't do that,
even with Jaz Hoyt,

28:11.367 --> 28:13.467
you shouldn't be here.

28:13.467 --> 28:15.633
- I'm--I'm sorry.

28:15.633 --> 28:18.333
You're right, as usual.

28:18.333 --> 28:20.633
Let me--let me
make it up to you.

28:20.633 --> 28:22.033
Are you--
are you free for lunch?

28:23.433 --> 28:25.133
- No, actually.

28:25.133 --> 28:28.100
I'm in the middle of trying
to locate Hoyt's birth mother.

28:28.100 --> 28:30.133
- Why?

28:30.133 --> 28:32.500
- I want to know
where Hoyt came from.

28:32.500 --> 28:34.467
- In order to save him?

28:34.467 --> 28:37.066
- Well, yes.

28:38.500 --> 28:41.133
- You are a remarkable man, Ray.

28:41.133 --> 28:45.133
You are a saint.
- Hardly.

28:45.133 --> 28:49.400
- Well, if you won't have lunch
with me, how about dinner?

28:49.400 --> 28:52.567
You haven't eaten unless
you've tasted my roast chicken.

28:52.567 --> 28:54.800
I won't take no
for an answer.

28:55.767 --> 28:58.400
- All right,
I'd be delighted.

28:58.400 --> 28:59.800
- Great.

28:59.800 --> 29:01.533
7:30?

29:14.467 --> 29:19.033
- He was only one day old
when I gave him up for adoption.

29:19.033 --> 29:22.467
My boyfriend had just
been sent to prison,

29:22.467 --> 29:26.767
and my parents thought that
I should have a chance at life.

29:26.767 --> 29:30.400
Buster was a real bastard.

29:30.400 --> 29:35.600
You should excuse me, Father,
but he was a slimeball.

29:35.600 --> 29:38.734
My husband, John,

29:38.734 --> 29:42.700
he's a sweet, sweet man.

29:42.700 --> 29:44.467
I gotta tell you,

29:44.467 --> 29:48.066
I'm real nervous
about seeing my son.

29:48.066 --> 29:51.100
I actually thought
to call and cancel.

29:51.100 --> 29:54.467
- I'll be with you
every step.

29:54.467 --> 29:57.233
- Thank you.

29:57.233 --> 29:58.734
- Mrs. Oppenheimer,

29:58.734 --> 30:02.934
Jaz is in an extremely
volatile mental state.

30:02.934 --> 30:05.667
He may say terrible,
terrible things.

30:07.767 --> 30:11.000
- I have no expectations,
Father.

30:12.967 --> 30:16.266
I only hope that...

30:16.266 --> 30:20.533
I hope that my visit
can help make my son whole.

30:23.567 --> 30:25.667
- Are you ready, Jaz?

30:25.667 --> 30:27.867
- Uh-huh.

30:36.500 --> 30:40.934
- Hi.
- Mama, hello.

30:54.266 --> 30:57.066
- Well, we'll see you
at 12:00 noon tomorrow then.

30:57.066 --> 30:59.233
Excellent.

30:59.233 --> 31:01.900
Thanks again
for everything.

31:05.066 --> 31:07.066
Okay, goodbye.

31:08.767 --> 31:10.333
- Working late?

31:10.333 --> 31:12.800
- Well, yes.

31:14.133 --> 31:16.467
- I've been trying to do
what you suggested,

31:16.467 --> 31:20.133
to separate the man
from the crime,

31:20.133 --> 31:22.934
but I don't know, I see Hoyt
every day in the hospital ward,

31:22.934 --> 31:24.800
and the two seem
to be intertwined.

31:26.800 --> 31:28.333
- There are many,
many places

31:28.333 --> 31:29.734
looking for
qualified nurses, Jessica.

31:29.734 --> 31:31.100
I could help you.

31:31.100 --> 31:33.633
- Well, then we would
never see each other.

31:33.633 --> 31:38.934
- Look, I'm certainly not your
only reason for working in Oz.

31:38.934 --> 31:42.000
- Not my only reason, no,

31:42.000 --> 31:44.900
but I have
so few close friends.

31:47.734 --> 31:49.467
Here, let me.

32:00.033 --> 32:01.934
- Please, stop that.

32:01.934 --> 32:03.400
- Stop what?

32:04.934 --> 32:07.400
- Stop touching me.

32:07.400 --> 32:09.600
- Oh, I'm sorry.

32:09.600 --> 32:14.066
- No, I'm sorry that
I can't be more to you.

32:14.066 --> 32:17.633
- What do you mean?

32:17.633 --> 32:20.133
- I took a vow of celibacy.

32:20.133 --> 32:21.633
- Cel--

32:21.633 --> 32:23.533
do you--

32:25.567 --> 32:27.200
How dare you?

32:27.200 --> 32:29.400
I am a good
Catholic woman.

32:29.400 --> 32:32.166
I have been all my life.
- That's not what--

32:32.166 --> 32:35.667
- How dare you
have such thoughts?

32:35.667 --> 32:37.633
My son was right
about you,

32:37.633 --> 32:42.300
you are nothing but a fucking
slanty-eyed mongrel!

32:47.133 --> 32:51.100
- You do something for me;
kill Timmy Kirk.

32:51.100 --> 32:54.066
- What the--
- Ahh!

32:54.066 --> 32:55.467
- Ugh!

32:57.400 --> 33:00.367
- Ray, Ray.
Listen to this.

33:00.367 --> 33:03.533
After his mother left,
Jaz Hoyt really opened up.

33:03.533 --> 33:05.800
He told me it was
the Reverend Cloutier

33:05.800 --> 33:09.834
who ordered him to kill
Timmy Kirk the first time.

33:09.834 --> 33:11.667
- Well, how is
that possible?

33:11.667 --> 33:12.967
Cloutier was
in the burn unit.

33:12.967 --> 33:14.333
He was barely able
to make sounds,

33:14.333 --> 33:15.800
let alone speak.

33:15.800 --> 33:18.266
- Well, he says that Cloutier
appeared to him in his cell

33:18.266 --> 33:20.633
looking
completely normal.

33:22.033 --> 33:24.467
- An apparition?

33:24.467 --> 33:26.500
- Afterward, when he was
sent to solitary,

33:26.500 --> 33:28.567
his biker buddies
decided to take revenge.

33:28.567 --> 33:31.533
They went to the burn unit
and carried Cloutier away.

33:31.533 --> 33:32.834
- To where?

33:32.834 --> 33:35.734
- Well, Hoyt says
that's the one fact

33:35.734 --> 33:37.867
he will reveal
only to you.

33:40.467 --> 33:43.100
- Where did they take
the reverend Cloutier?

33:43.100 --> 33:44.700
- If I tell you,

33:44.700 --> 33:47.934
the other bikers,
they'll kill us both.

33:47.934 --> 33:51.600
- Hoyt, I need to know.

33:54.867 --> 33:56.600
- Okay.

35:05.867 --> 35:07.633
- Here's a story,
and it's true.

35:07.633 --> 35:09.066
A male prisoner

35:09.066 --> 35:11.166
at the Muskegon Correctional
Facility in Michigan

35:11.166 --> 35:13.367
sexually assaulted
the three-year-old daughter

35:13.367 --> 35:14.834
of a woman
who was visiting him.

35:14.834 --> 35:16.133
As a result,

35:16.133 --> 35:18.367
the State DOC came up
with the harshest,

35:18.367 --> 35:20.567
most restrictive
visiting policies

35:20.567 --> 35:22.333
of anywhere
in the country,

35:22.333 --> 35:24.133
which included
the banning of all minors,

35:24.133 --> 35:26.100
even family members.

35:26.100 --> 35:28.433
So you see,
one man's fuck-up

35:28.433 --> 35:31.000
fucked up
everybody else's happiness.

35:33.900 --> 35:35.867
- Redding, I have
to talk to you.

35:37.333 --> 35:39.533
I feel guilty lying
to my brothers,

35:39.533 --> 35:41.567
telling them
the book binding machinery

35:41.567 --> 35:44.133
was destroyed
by accident.

35:44.133 --> 35:46.800
- Did you get your check
from the insurance company?

35:49.734 --> 35:52.500
So none of you all
lost any money,

35:52.500 --> 35:55.800
which you sure as shit would
have when the company folded.

35:55.800 --> 35:58.567
- The money is
not the issue.

35:58.567 --> 36:03.533
You committed a criminal act,
and I'm benefitting from it.

36:03.533 --> 36:05.533
I have to do
something.

36:05.533 --> 36:08.266
- Whatever you do will
destroy your reputation

36:08.266 --> 36:09.967
with your brothers
over there.

36:11.300 --> 36:13.033
Can you live
with that?

36:40.400 --> 36:42.667
- You gonna tell me
what that was all about?

36:42.667 --> 36:45.433
- I was coming
to see you next,

36:45.433 --> 36:47.500
to make
a full confession.

36:49.166 --> 36:52.266
- I'm all ears,
as they say.

36:52.266 --> 36:55.233
- The accident which destroyed
the book-binding machinery

36:55.233 --> 36:57.500
was not an accident.

36:57.500 --> 36:59.700
Burr Redding
is responsible.

37:01.200 --> 37:03.200
- Why jabber now?

37:03.200 --> 37:05.400
- Because I feel guilty.

37:05.400 --> 37:09.600
I disgraced the memory
of Kareem Said.

37:09.600 --> 37:11.200
Each night
when I pray,

37:11.200 --> 37:14.300
the words become more
and more hollow.

37:14.300 --> 37:17.500
My soul is in peril.

37:20.667 --> 37:22.867
- I have to punish you.

37:22.867 --> 37:24.734
Officer.

37:27.667 --> 37:28.834
Take him back
to Em City,

37:28.834 --> 37:30.300
put him
in the cage.

37:32.867 --> 37:35.433
- I don't know what you're
talking about, McManus.

37:35.433 --> 37:38.400
I haven't been anywhere near
that book-binding machinery.

37:38.400 --> 37:40.400
- Arif says
you sent someone.

37:40.400 --> 37:42.333
- Arif is delusional.

37:42.333 --> 37:43.967
- What's going on?

37:43.967 --> 37:46.800
- I'm afraid you're gonna have
to find a new foreman, Donna.

37:46.800 --> 37:49.734
Redding's taking an early
retirement in solitary.

37:49.734 --> 37:51.233
- You got no proof.

