1:19:39.467 --> 1:19:40.867
he didn't say
is not proof.

1:19:40.867 --> 1:19:44.200
Tobias, we live
in a nation of laws,

1:19:44.200 --> 1:19:45.934
some of which
are inspired

1:19:45.934 --> 1:19:47.367
and some of which
are just lousy.

1:19:47.367 --> 1:19:50.734
But we can't
abandon our moral code

1:19:50.734 --> 1:19:53.100
whenever
it's convenient.

1:19:53.100 --> 1:19:56.033
Then we might as well
just open all the gates

1:19:56.033 --> 1:19:57.533
of all the prisons.

1:20:01.066 --> 1:20:03.633
- I want to be
with my children.

1:20:06.700 --> 1:20:09.800
- My dear Tobias,

1:20:09.800 --> 1:20:12.667
in all my years
sitting across that desk,

1:20:12.667 --> 1:20:15.300
I have learned
one thing.

1:20:15.300 --> 1:20:17.800
Most people who come
to me with a problem

1:20:17.800 --> 1:20:21.500
have already made up their minds
how they'll proceed.

1:20:21.500 --> 1:20:24.333
They're just here hoping
I'll agree with them,

1:20:24.333 --> 1:20:27.266
hoping I'll make them
feel better.

1:20:27.266 --> 1:20:29.834
I can't do that with you.

1:20:33.500 --> 1:20:35.467
I gotta go.

1:20:35.467 --> 1:20:37.333
Tonight's opening
night of "Macbeth."

1:20:37.333 --> 1:20:39.133
I have to get ready.

1:20:56.233 --> 1:20:58.266
Miguel,
are you okay?

1:20:58.266 --> 1:21:01.166
- Just a little
opening night jitters,

1:21:01.166 --> 1:21:03.700
a little cotton--
cotton mouth.

1:21:03.700 --> 1:21:05.867
- Okay.
You set?

1:21:05.867 --> 1:21:07.266
- Let's make
theatrical history.

1:21:07.266 --> 1:21:09.233
- All right.
You guys ready?

1:21:09.233 --> 1:21:11.500
- I'm so excited
I'm gonna bust my buttons.

1:21:11.500 --> 1:21:13.233
- Don't do that,
it's a rental.

1:21:13.233 --> 1:21:15.100
All right, everybody,
we worked hard,

1:21:15.100 --> 1:21:16.867
so now's the time
to have fun.

1:21:16.867 --> 1:21:18.734
So, if you flub a line,
just keep going.

1:21:18.734 --> 1:21:21.533
If you miss a cue,
don't panic.

1:21:21.533 --> 1:21:23.567
I'm very proud
of all of you.

1:21:23.567 --> 1:21:25.333
Break a leg.

1:21:28.800 --> 1:21:30.734
- Have a good show,
Beecher.

1:21:36.834 --> 1:21:39.266
- Miguel,
dim the house lights.

1:21:54.066 --> 1:21:55.367
Good evening,

1:21:55.367 --> 1:21:56.934
and welcome
to the premiere production

1:21:56.934 --> 1:21:58.834
of the Oswald players.

1:21:58.834 --> 1:22:02.033
Before we begin, there are
a few changes in the program.

1:22:02.033 --> 1:22:05.700
The second Weird Sister
will be played by Reggie Rawls

1:22:05.700 --> 1:22:07.433
instead of
Chico Guerra.

1:22:07.433 --> 1:22:09.767
Banquo will be played
by Tom Smeeding

1:22:09.767 --> 1:22:11.734
instead of
Agamemnon Busmalis.

1:22:11.734 --> 1:22:14.333
And Norman Duttweiler
will play King Duncan

1:22:14.333 --> 1:22:16.433
instead of
Burr Redding.

1:22:16.433 --> 1:22:19.533
I would also like to say
that Warden Leo Glynn

1:22:19.533 --> 1:22:22.533
was a great supporter
of bringing the arts to Oz,

1:22:22.533 --> 1:22:25.500
and so, we dedicate
tonight's performance

1:22:25.500 --> 1:22:27.767
in his memory,

1:22:27.767 --> 1:22:31.066
and also to the memory
of Cyril O'Reily.

1:22:31.066 --> 1:22:32.734
Thank you.

1:22:41.000 --> 1:22:43.400
They spent some money
on this shit.

1:22:47.300 --> 1:22:49.467
- When shall we three
meet again?

1:22:49.467 --> 1:22:52.567
In thunder,
lightning or in rain?

1:22:52.567 --> 1:22:55.066
- When the hurlyburly's done,

1:22:55.066 --> 1:22:57.767
when the battle's lost and won.

1:22:57.767 --> 1:23:00.934
- That will be
the set of sun.

1:23:00.934 --> 1:23:03.900
- Where the place?
- Upon the heath.

1:23:03.900 --> 1:23:06.633
There to meet with Macbeth.

1:23:11.066 --> 1:23:13.767
- Everlasting bonfire...

1:23:13.767 --> 1:23:16.867
- Anon! Anon!

1:23:16.867 --> 1:23:20.133
I pray you, remember
the porter!

1:23:24.734 --> 1:23:26.500
- Hie thee hither,

1:23:26.500 --> 1:23:30.000
that I may pour
my spirits in thine ear

1:23:30.000 --> 1:23:33.400
and chastise with
the valor of my tongue

1:23:33.400 --> 1:23:36.233
all that impedes thee
from the golden round

1:23:36.233 --> 1:23:38.700
which fate
and metaphysical aid...

1:23:38.700 --> 1:23:40.033
- Miguel.

1:23:40.033 --> 1:23:42.300
- Doth seem to have
three crowned withal.

1:23:47.533 --> 1:23:50.100
- what is thy name?

1:23:50.100 --> 1:23:52.967
- Thou'lt be afraid
to hear it.

1:23:52.967 --> 1:23:56.066
- No, though thy callest
thyself a hotter name,

1:23:56.066 --> 1:23:58.200
than any is in hell.

1:24:02.000 --> 1:24:03.700
- My name's Macbeth.

1:24:21.400 --> 1:24:24.467
- Toby, I've got a plan,
a way to get Schillinger

1:24:24.467 --> 1:24:25.767
out of our lives
forever.

1:24:25.767 --> 1:24:26.867
- I don't want to hear it.

1:24:26.867 --> 1:24:29.133
- Toby--
- Just give me my prop.

1:24:47.567 --> 1:24:50.967
- Thou was born of women,
but swords I smile at,

1:24:50.967 --> 1:24:53.233
weapons laugh to scorn,

1:24:53.233 --> 1:24:56.533
brandished by man
that's of a woman born.

1:24:56.533 --> 1:24:58.133
- Turn!

1:24:58.133 --> 1:24:59.934
Hellhound, turn!

1:25:01.767 --> 1:25:05.333
- Of all men else
I have avoided thee.

1:25:06.800 --> 1:25:08.800
But get thee back.

1:25:08.800 --> 1:25:12.166
My soul is too much charged
with blood of thine already.

1:25:12.166 --> 1:25:14.033
- I have no words.

1:25:14.033 --> 1:25:16.266
My voice is in my sword,

1:25:16.266 --> 1:25:19.367
thou bloodier villain
than terms can give thee out.

1:25:19.367 --> 1:25:21.567
man: Stick him, stick him!

1:25:27.533 --> 1:25:29.333
- You're a dead man,
sweetpea.

1:25:35.700 --> 1:25:39.433
That cocksucker.

1:25:49.266 --> 1:25:50.333
- Dr. Nathan!

1:25:50.333 --> 1:25:52.133
- That motherfucker's dead.

1:25:59.300 --> 1:26:03.400
- Hey, get back!
Get the fuck back!

1:26:03.400 --> 1:26:04.834
- As you know,
we're investigating

1:26:04.834 --> 1:26:06.867
what happened on the stage.

1:26:06.867 --> 1:26:09.266
Trying to determine
whether Schillinger's death

1:26:09.266 --> 1:26:11.667
was accidental
or intentional.

1:26:11.667 --> 1:26:13.567
- Chris Keller says
he handed you the knife

1:26:13.567 --> 1:26:15.700
just before your entrance.

1:26:15.700 --> 1:26:18.066
- How did a real knife
get on the prop table?

1:26:18.066 --> 1:26:19.867
- I don't know.

1:26:19.867 --> 1:26:22.100
- Suzanne Fitzgerald says
there were no problems

1:26:22.100 --> 1:26:23.467
during the rehearsals.

1:26:23.467 --> 1:26:25.600
- Schillinger and Keller
seemed very friendly.

1:26:25.600 --> 1:26:28.133
They were horsing around
and stuff.

1:26:28.133 --> 1:26:29.667
- What about Beecher?

1:26:29.667 --> 1:26:31.500
- He--he seemed fine.

1:26:31.500 --> 1:26:35.633
Distant, but not in
the least bit confrontational.

1:26:35.633 --> 1:26:37.800
- All of which jibes
with the statement you made

1:26:37.800 --> 1:26:40.567
immediately after
you stabbed Schillinger.

1:26:40.567 --> 1:26:43.400
Do you have anything
to add at this time?

1:26:43.400 --> 1:26:45.433
- No, sir.

1:26:45.433 --> 1:26:46.967
- Okay.

1:26:46.967 --> 1:26:50.467
We've decided to rule
that Schillinger's death

1:26:50.467 --> 1:26:52.533
was accidental.

1:26:52.533 --> 1:26:54.967
- You're coming back
to Em City.

1:26:57.200 --> 1:26:58.834
- Thank you.

1:26:59.800 --> 1:27:01.233
Thank you, all.

1:27:18.367 --> 1:27:19.900
What are you
doing here?

1:27:19.900 --> 1:27:22.333
- I asked Querns
to transfer me back.

1:27:22.333 --> 1:27:24.200
I guess he
convinced McManus.

1:27:24.200 --> 1:27:27.333
Even made us roomies.

1:27:27.333 --> 1:27:29.900
- No.
- Yeah.

1:27:29.900 --> 1:27:32.500
- Nothing's changed, Chris.

1:27:32.500 --> 1:27:35.166
- I know, you've got
the top bunk just like before.

1:27:35.166 --> 1:27:38.700
- I mean my feelings
haven't changed.

1:27:40.133 --> 1:27:41.367
I'm gonna
go to McManus,

1:27:41.367 --> 1:27:42.734
ask him to move me
to another pod,

1:27:42.734 --> 1:27:44.066
- Toby.
- Move me to Gen Pop.

1:27:44.066 --> 1:27:45.400
- Toby, goddamn it.

1:27:45.400 --> 1:27:47.400
- Look, will you get it
through your head,

1:27:47.400 --> 1:27:49.867
I don't want you
in my life.

1:27:52.000 --> 1:27:54.133
- After everything
I've done for you.

1:27:54.133 --> 1:27:57.233
- Yeah, like almost getting me
sent to death row.

1:27:57.233 --> 1:27:58.500
- Hey, if it weren't
for me, pal,

1:27:58.500 --> 1:27:59.967
you'd be in the morgue
instead of Schillinger.

1:27:59.967 --> 1:28:02.700
- Maybe.
- Yeah.

1:28:02.700 --> 1:28:05.100
- But if you think I got any
satisfaction out of killing him,

1:28:05.100 --> 1:28:07.000
you're wrong.

1:28:07.000 --> 1:28:08.834
You don't know
me at all.

1:28:08.834 --> 1:28:11.000
- I don't know you?

1:28:11.000 --> 1:28:13.266
I know you're free
of that Nazi fuck.

1:28:16.667 --> 1:28:18.300
- No, I'm not.

1:28:19.767 --> 1:28:22.100
No more free than
I am of his two sons,

1:28:22.100 --> 1:28:26.600
or Metzger
or Cathy Rockwell.

1:28:33.867 --> 1:28:37.166
Chris, after six years
in this place,

1:28:37.166 --> 1:28:41.066
I'm not sure about
anything anymore.

1:28:41.066 --> 1:28:44.500
Heaven, justice...

1:28:44.500 --> 1:28:47.967
Truth.

1:28:47.967 --> 1:28:53.200
The only thing I believe in
is life.

1:28:53.200 --> 1:28:55.166
Every life
is precious.

1:28:55.166 --> 1:28:56.734
Not just
yours or mine,

1:28:56.734 --> 1:28:59.700
but every single person
on the planet who's breathing,

1:28:59.700 --> 1:29:03.600
their lives
are precious.

1:29:03.600 --> 1:29:07.300
And the loss of
a single life, even in Oz,

1:29:07.300 --> 1:29:09.200
is my loss too.

1:29:10.867 --> 1:29:13.133
- Well, that's bullshit.

1:29:13.133 --> 1:29:15.867
The only thing
that matters is you and me.

1:29:18.166 --> 1:29:20.200
- I don't expect you
to understand.

1:29:20.200 --> 1:29:23.000
You kill for sport.

1:29:23.000 --> 1:29:25.066
- I don't understand?

1:29:25.066 --> 1:29:28.600
I'm not the one who
got here by accident, pal.

1:29:28.600 --> 1:29:30.900
I kill
because I have to.

1:29:30.900 --> 1:29:34.800
I kill what stands
in my way,

1:29:34.800 --> 1:29:38.266
like the Aryans.

1:29:38.266 --> 1:29:39.700
- What?

1:29:39.700 --> 1:29:41.300
What about the Aryans?

1:29:41.300 --> 1:29:42.800
- They're no threat
to us anymore.

1:29:42.800 --> 1:29:44.934
I took care of that.

1:29:44.934 --> 1:29:46.300
- How?
How'd you take care of it?

1:29:46.300 --> 1:29:47.600
- Never mind, kiss me.

1:29:47.600 --> 1:29:49.233
- Wait.

1:29:53.967 --> 1:29:56.200
Answer me
this first, okay?

1:29:58.467 --> 1:30:00.467
I want you
to be honest, okay?

1:30:05.300 --> 1:30:07.467
Did you purposely
fuck up my parole?

1:30:22.667 --> 1:30:24.900
- Toby, I couldn't face
the rest of my life

1:30:24.900 --> 1:30:26.734
living in here
without you.

1:30:29.800 --> 1:30:32.033
Don't you see?
I did what I did out of love.

1:30:34.567 --> 1:30:37.567
- If you really love me,

1:30:37.567 --> 1:30:40.367
then leave me alone.

1:30:46.033 --> 1:30:47.600
- I can't.

1:30:47.600 --> 1:30:49.867
- Listen to me.
Listen to me.

1:30:49.867 --> 1:30:51.367
I loved alcohol.

1:30:51.367 --> 1:30:53.400
I loved heroin.

1:30:53.400 --> 1:30:56.967
I had to put them behind me
because they were poison.

1:30:58.867 --> 1:31:00.100
Death.

1:31:03.867 --> 1:31:06.000
You are death.

1:31:07.800 --> 1:31:09.500
Let me live.

1:31:23.200 --> 1:31:26.367
- I can't.
- Motherfucker!

1:31:26.367 --> 1:31:29.233
- Toby, I love you.

1:31:29.233 --> 1:31:30.800
Beecher, don't!

1:31:30.800 --> 1:31:32.767
- No!

1:31:32.767 --> 1:31:34.300
No!
- No!

1:31:57.200 --> 1:32:00.300
God is a funny fellow,
Sister.

1:32:02.333 --> 1:32:06.066
See, I decided this morning
to cooperate with the FBI

1:32:06.066 --> 1:32:07.800
to help them
convict Keller.

1:32:07.800 --> 1:32:08.900
- Oh?

1:32:08.900 --> 1:32:13.667
- And now,
with Keller dead,

1:32:13.667 --> 1:32:16.400
that opportunity
is gone,

1:32:16.400 --> 1:32:20.133
and with it,
my chance for freedom.

1:32:20.133 --> 1:32:24.967
In fact, I may be
facing the death penalty

1:32:24.967 --> 1:32:26.633
for Keller's murder.

1:32:26.633 --> 1:32:29.100
- You didn't push him,
did you?

1:32:29.100 --> 1:32:30.767
- No.

1:32:32.834 --> 1:32:36.900
- Well, let's hope this time
the truth works for you.

1:32:36.900 --> 1:32:41.233
- You know, he said he did
what he did out of love.

1:32:41.233 --> 1:32:43.934
- Oh, love is used

1:32:43.934 --> 1:32:48.066
as an excuse
for so many things.

1:32:48.066 --> 1:32:51.333
- No.

1:32:51.333 --> 1:32:54.767
He really did
love me, Sister.

1:32:54.767 --> 1:32:57.934
- Yes.

1:32:57.934 --> 1:32:59.767
- And I loved him.

1:33:02.400 --> 1:33:06.734
When God was
designing the universe,

1:33:06.734 --> 1:33:09.567
why did he make
something so wonderful

1:33:09.567 --> 1:33:12.400
so fucking painful?

1:33:13.533 --> 1:33:16.800
- I think he thought
we could handle it.

1:33:16.800 --> 1:33:18.834
- Beecher.

1:33:18.834 --> 1:33:21.233
I'm going to move you
back to Unit J.

1:33:21.233 --> 1:33:22.834
I'm concerned
about the Aryans

1:33:22.834 --> 1:33:25.000
taking revenge on you
for Schillinger.

1:33:25.000 --> 1:33:27.333
- I said the same thing
to Keller, and he said,

1:33:27.333 --> 1:33:30.300
"Don't worry,
I've handled the Aryans."

1:33:30.300 --> 1:33:32.700
- What did he mean by that?

1:33:45.000 --> 1:33:46.900
- Hey, Andenaur,
check it out.

1:33:46.900 --> 1:33:49.500
You got a package.

1:33:49.500 --> 1:33:53.433
- Hmm, no name,

1:33:53.433 --> 1:33:56.000
no return address.

1:34:01.233 --> 1:34:03.934
What the fuck is this?
- I don't know.

1:34:17.533 --> 1:34:21.100
- They're all  dead?
- Yes, plus two C.O.'s.

1:34:21.100 --> 1:34:23.300
- From what?
- I'm not sure, but it could be

1:34:23.300 --> 1:34:25.266
any number of toxins
or chemicals.

1:34:25.266 --> 1:34:26.834
I cordoned off the area,
but I've got to tell you,

1:34:26.834 --> 1:34:28.567
this is way beyond
my expertise.

1:34:28.567 --> 1:34:29.767
- What do we do?

1:34:29.767 --> 1:34:31.000
- Call the state
bio-terrorism unit,

1:34:31.000 --> 1:34:34.300
and clear out
the entire complex, fast!

1:34:34.300 --> 1:34:36.734
- Proceed immediately
to level one,

1:34:36.734 --> 1:34:38.834
emergency evacuation.

1:34:38.834 --> 1:34:40.467
- Where are we going
to take them?

1:34:40.467 --> 1:34:41.934
- Beats the shit
out of me.

1:34:41.934 --> 1:34:43.400
All I've been told is

1:34:43.400 --> 1:34:45.033
the move is temporary.

1:34:45.033 --> 1:34:46.266
We'll be back,
someday.

1:34:46.266 --> 1:34:48.834
- Emergency evacuation.

1:34:55.500 --> 1:34:57.567
- I said everybody out!

1:35:07.834 --> 1:35:09.834
- Come on, move it!

1:35:09.834 --> 1:35:12.133
- Let's go! Let's go

1:35:17.734 --> 1:35:19.000
- Let's go!

1:35:21.100 --> 1:35:23.800
- Give me a blanket!
- Shut up and move!

1:35:24.867 --> 1:35:26.433
- Let's go,
Come on, let's go!

1:35:26.433 --> 1:35:27.867
- All right, come on.
Come on.

1:35:30.500 --> 1:35:32.800
- Back of the bus first.

1:35:32.800 --> 1:35:35.033
Move to the back
of the bus.

1:36:28.800 --> 1:36:31.033
- Count!

1:36:31.033 --> 1:36:33.633
- A lot of people thought
we'd never reopen Emerald City.

1:36:33.633 --> 1:36:35.667
- Came out like
nothing was happening...

1:36:35.667 --> 1:36:37.200
- I killed a man.

1:36:39.066 --> 1:36:40.633
- Fuck you.
- Help!

1:36:40.633 --> 1:36:42.834
- Lights out, O'Reily.

1:36:42.834 --> 1:36:44.633
- Settle down!

1:36:44.633 --> 1:36:46.533
- Officer!

1:36:51.767 --> 1:36:54.533
- The bikers, the Christians,
the gays...

1:36:54.533 --> 1:36:56.667
- Follow routine.

1:36:56.667 --> 1:37:01.567
- We tell you when to sleep,
when to eat,

1:37:01.567 --> 1:37:03.600
when to piss.

1:37:33.066 --> 1:37:35.600
- So, what have
we learned?

1:37:35.600 --> 1:37:38.033
What's the lesson
for today,

1:37:38.033 --> 1:37:41.867
for all the never-ending days
and restless nights in Oz?

1:37:41.867 --> 1:37:44.533
That morality
is transient?

1:37:44.533 --> 1:37:49.433
That virtue cannot exist
without violence?

1:37:49.433 --> 1:37:53.433
That to be honest
is to be flawed?

1:37:53.433 --> 1:37:55.867
That the giving
and taking of love,

1:37:55.867 --> 1:37:59.066
both debases
and elevates us?

1:37:59.066 --> 1:38:04.300
That God or Allah or Yahweh
has answer to questions

1:38:04.300 --> 1:38:07.567
we dare not even ask?

1:38:07.567 --> 1:38:09.934
The story is simple.

1:38:09.934 --> 1:38:13.233
A man lives
in prison and dies.

1:38:13.233 --> 1:38:17.200
How he dies,
that's easy.

1:38:17.200 --> 1:38:21.967
The who and the why
is the complex part,

1:38:21.967 --> 1:38:25.533
the human part,

1:38:25.533 --> 1:38:29.433
the only part worth...

